1190  if ( (tn + h - tstop)*h > ZERO )
1191  h = (tstop - tn)*(ONE-FOUR*uround);
1192  }
1193 
1194  /* Scale zn[1] by h.*/
1195 
1196  hscale = h;
1197  h0u = h;
1198  hprime = h;
1199 
1200  N_VScale(h, zn[1], zn[1]);
1201 
1202  /* Check for zeros of root function g at and near t0. */
1203 
1204  if (nrtfn > 0) {
1205 
1206  retval = cvRcheck1(cv_mem);
1207 
1208  if (retval == CV_RTFUNC_FAIL) {
1209  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_RTFUNC_FAIL, "CVODE", "cvRcheck1", MSGCV_RTFUNC_FAILED, tn);
1210  return(CV_RTFUNC_FAIL);
1211  }
1212 
1213  }
1214 
1215  } /* end of first call block */
1216 
1217  /*
1218  * ------------------------------------------------------
1219  * 3. At following steps, perform stop tests:
1220  * - check for root in last step
1221  * - check if we passed tstop
1222  * - check if we passed tout (NORMAL mode)
1223  * - check if current tn was returned (ONE_STEP mode)
1224  * - check if we are close to tstop
1225  * (adjust step size if needed)
1226  * -------------------------------------------------------
1227  */
1228 
1229  if (nst > 0) {
1230 
1231  /* Estimate an infinitesimal time interval to be used as
1232  a roundoff for time quantities (based on current time
1233  and step size) */
1234  troundoff = FUZZ_FACTOR*uround*(SUNRabs(tn) + SUNRabs(h));
1235 
1236  /* First, check for a root in the last step taken, other than the
1237  last root found, if any. If itask = CV_ONE_STEP and y(tn) was not
1238  returned because of an intervening root, return y(tn) now. */
1239  if (nrtfn > 0) {
1240 
1241  irfndp = irfnd;
1242 
1243  retval = cvRcheck2(cv_mem);
1244 
1245  if (retval == CLOSERT) {
1246  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_ILL_INPUT, "CVODE", "cvRcheck2", MSGCV_CLOSE_ROOTS, tlo);
1247  return(CV_ILL_INPUT);
1248  } else if (retval == CV_RTFUNC_FAIL) {
1249  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_RTFUNC_FAIL, "CVODE", "cvRcheck2", MSGCV_RTFUNC_FAILED, tlo);
1250  return(CV_RTFUNC_FAIL);
1251  } else if (retval == RTFOUND) {
1252  tretlast = *tret = tlo;
1253  return(CV_ROOT_RETURN);
1254  }
1255 
1256  /* If tn is distinct from tretlast (within roundoff),
1257  check remaining interval for roots */
1258  if ( SUNRabs(tn - tretlast) > troundoff ) {
1259 
1260  retval = cvRcheck3(cv_mem);
1261 
1262  if (retval == CV_SUCCESS) { /* no root found */
1263  irfnd = 0;
1264  if ((irfndp == 1) && (itask == CV_ONE_STEP)) {
1265  tretlast = *tret = tn;
1266  N_VScale(ONE, zn[0], yout);
1267  return(CV_SUCCESS);
1268  }
1269  } else if (retval == RTFOUND) { /* a new root was found */
1270  irfnd = 1;
1271  tretlast = *tret = tlo;
1272  return(CV_ROOT_RETURN);
1273  } else if (retval == CV_RTFUNC_FAIL) { /* g failed */
1274  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_RTFUNC_FAIL, "CVODE", "cvRcheck3", MSGCV_RTFUNC_FAILED, tlo);
1275  return(CV_RTFUNC_FAIL);
1276  }
1277 
1278  }
1279 
1280  } /* end of root stop check */
1281 
1282  /* In CV_NORMAL mode, test if tout was reached */
1283  if ( (itask == CV_NORMAL) && ((tn-tout)*h >= ZERO) ) {
1284  tretlast = *tret = tout;
1285  ier = CVodeGetDky(cv_mem, tout, 0, yout);
1286  if (ier != CV_SUCCESS) {
1287  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_ILL_INPUT, "CVODE", "CVode", MSGCV_BAD_TOUT, tout);
1288  return(CV_ILL_INPUT);
1289  }
1290  return(CV_SUCCESS);
1291  }
1292 
1293  /* In CV_ONE_STEP mode, test if tn was returned */
1294  if ( itask == CV_ONE_STEP && SUNRabs(tn - tretlast) > troundoff ) {
1295  tretlast = *tret = tn;
1296  N_VScale(ONE, zn[0], yout);
1297  return(CV_SUCCESS);
1298  }
1299 
1300  /* Test for tn at tstop or near tstop */
1301  if ( tstopset ) {
1302 
1303  if ( SUNRabs(tn - tstop) <= troundoff) {
1304  ier = CVodeGetDky(cv_mem, tstop, 0, yout);
1305  if (ier != CV_SUCCESS) {
1306  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_ILL_INPUT, "CVODE", "CVode", MSGCV_BAD_TSTOP, tstop, tn);
1307  return(CV_ILL_INPUT);
1308  }
1309  tretlast = *tret = tstop;
1310  tstopset = FALSE;
1311  return(CV_TSTOP_RETURN);
1312  }
1313 
1314  /* If next step would overtake tstop, adjust stepsize */
1315  if ( (tn + hprime - tstop)*h > ZERO ) {
1316  hprime = (tstop - tn)*(ONE-FOUR*uround);
1317  eta = hprime/h;
1318  }
1319 
1320  }
1321 
1322  } /* end stopping tests block */
1323 
1324  /*
1325  * --------------------------------------------------
1326  * 4. Looping point for internal steps
1327  *
1328  * 4.1. check for errors (too many steps, too much
1329  * accuracy requested, step size too small)
1330  * 4.2. take a new step (call cvStep)
1331  * 4.3. stop on error
1332  * 4.4. perform stop tests:
1333  * - check for root in last step
1334  * - check if tout was passed
1335  * - check if close to tstop
1336  * - check if in ONE_STEP mode (must return)
1337  * --------------------------------------------------
1338  */
1339 
1340  nstloc = 0;
1341  loop {
1342 
1343  next_h = h;
1344  next_q = q;
1345 
1346  /* Reset and check ewt */
1347  if (nst > 0) {
1348 
1349  ewtsetOK = efun(zn[0], ewt, e_data);
1350 
1351  if (ewtsetOK != 0) {
1352 
1353  if (itol == CV_WF)
1354  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_ILL_INPUT, "CVODE", "CVode", MSGCV_EWT_NOW_FAIL, tn);
1355  else
1356  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_ILL_INPUT, "CVODE", "CVode", MSGCV_EWT_NOW_BAD, tn);
1357 
1358  istate = CV_ILL_INPUT;
1359  tretlast = *tret = tn;
1360  N_VScale(ONE, zn[0], yout);
1361  break;
1362 
1363  }
1364  }
1365 
1366  /* Check for too many steps */
1367  if ( (mxstep>0) && (nstloc >= mxstep) ) {
1368  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_TOO_MUCH_WORK, "CVODE", "CVode", MSGCV_MAX_STEPS, tn);
1369  istate = CV_TOO_MUCH_WORK;
1370  tretlast = *tret = tn;
1371  N_VScale(ONE, zn[0], yout);
1372  break;
1373  }
1374 
1375  /* Check for too much accuracy requested */
1376  nrm = N_VWrmsNorm(zn[0], ewt);
1377  tolsf = uround * nrm;
1378  if (tolsf > ONE) {
1379  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_TOO_MUCH_ACC, "CVODE", "CVode", MSGCV_TOO_MUCH_ACC, tn);
1380  istate = CV_TOO_MUCH_ACC;
1381  tretlast = *tret = tn;
1382  N_VScale(ONE, zn[0], yout);
1383  tolsf *= TWO;
1384  break;
1385  } else {
1386  tolsf = ONE;
1387  }
1388 
1389  /* Check for h below roundoff level in tn */
1390  if (tn + h == tn) {
1391  nhnil++;
1392  if (nhnil <= mxhnil)
1393  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_WARNING, "CVODE", "CVode", MSGCV_HNIL, tn, h);
1394  if (nhnil == mxhnil)
1395  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_WARNING, "CVODE", "CVode", MSGCV_HNIL_DONE);
1396  }
1397 
1398  /* Call cvStep to take a step */
1399  kflag = cvStep(cv_mem);
1400 
1401  /* Process failed step cases, and exit loop */
1402  if (kflag != CV_SUCCESS) {
1403  istate = cvHandleFailure(cv_mem, kflag);
1404  tretlast = *tret = tn;
1405  N_VScale(ONE, zn[0], yout);
1406  break;
1407  }
1408 
1409  nstloc++;
1410 
1411  /* Check for root in last step taken. */
1412  if (nrtfn > 0) {
1413 
1414  retval = cvRcheck3(cv_mem);
1415 
1416  if (retval == RTFOUND) { /* A new root was found */
1417  irfnd = 1;
1418  istate = CV_ROOT_RETURN;
1419  tretlast = *tret = tlo;
1420  break;
1421  } else if (retval == CV_RTFUNC_FAIL) { /* g failed */
1422  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_RTFUNC_FAIL, "CVODE", "cvRcheck3", MSGCV_RTFUNC_FAILED, tlo);
1423  istate = CV_RTFUNC_FAIL;
1424  break;
1425  }
1426 
1427  /* If we are at the end of the first step and we still have
1428  * some event functions that are inactive, issue a warning
1429  * as this may indicate a user error in the implementation
1430  * of the root function. */
1431 
1432  if (nst==1) {
1433  inactive_roots = FALSE;
1434  for (ir=0; ir<nrtfn; ir++) {
1435  if (!gactive[ir]) {
1436  inactive_roots = TRUE;
1437  break;
1438  }
1439  }
1440  if ((cv_mem->cv_mxgnull > 0) && inactive_roots) {
1441  cvProcessError(cv_mem, CV_WARNING, "CVODES", "CVode", MSGCV_INACTIVE_ROOTS);
1442  }
1443  }
1444 
1445  }
1446 
1447  /* In NORMAL mode, check if tout reached */
1448  if ( (itask == CV_NORMAL) && (tn-tout)*h >= ZERO ) {
1449  istate = CV_SUCCESS;
1450  tretlast = *tret = tout;
1451  (void) CVodeGetDky(cv_mem, tout, 0, yout);
1452  next_q = qprime;
1453  next_h = hprime;
1454  break;
1455  }
1456 
1457  /* Check if tn is at tstop or near tstop */
1458  if ( tstopset ) {
1459 
1460  troundoff = FUZZ_FACTOR*uround*(SUNRabs(tn) + SUNRabs(h));
1461  if ( SUNRabs(tn - tstop) <= troundoff) {
1462  (void) CVodeGetDky(cv_mem, tstop, 0, yout);
1463  tretlast = *tret = tstop;
1464  tstopset = FALSE;
1465  istate = CV_TSTOP_RETURN;
1466  break;
1467  }
1468 
1469  if ( (tn + hprime - tstop)*h > ZERO ) {
1470  hprime = (tstop - tn)*(ONE-FOUR*uround);
1471  eta = hprime/h;
1472  }
1473 
1474  }
1475 
1476  /* In ONE_STEP mode, copy y and exit loop */
1477  if (itask == CV_ONE_STEP) {
1478  istate = CV_SUCCESS;
1479  tretlast = *tret = tn;
1480  N_VScale(ONE, zn[0], yout);
1481  next_q = qprime;
1482  next_h = hprime;
1483  break;
1484  }
1485 
1486  } /* end looping for internal steps */
1487 
1488  return(istate);
1489 }
